Description: Saccadous is a digital health startup providing hardware, software and analytics.
Full Description: Saccadous is a digital health startup dedicated to providing a non-invasive platform. The hardware, software, and analytics for diagnosing, and tracking. They include advancing the treatment of neurological diseases and other brain-related conditions like a traumatic brain injury. This is done through the capture and analysis of eye-movements at the microsaccade level or "fixational eye-movements".  During visual fixation, the eyes are never completely still, but produce small involuntary movements, called “fixational eye movements,” including microsaccades, drift, and tremor.  The research and intellectual property we have licensed has proven that microsaccade attributes such as magnitudes, velocities, durations, and intervals when compared show patterns that can be used to identify and differentiate subjects. The Saccadous solution (mobile, cloud-based & non-invasive) adds involuntary eye movements as a new evidence-based data source which we believe directly aligns with an aggressive and on ongoing Healthcare and Life Sciences transformation – the digital age in which mobile technologies, sensors, and advances in analytics make it possible to capture and decipher vast amounts of information.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Health Care, Information Technology

Description: NanoBio Designs offers an efficient detection platform to verify the presence or absence and levels of targeted genetic markers in samples.
Full Description: NanoBio Designs offers an efficient detection platform to verify the presence or absence and levels of targeted genetic markers in samples. Any and all TFA corps members can get a blog by registering with his or her TFA email address. Teach For Us was developed during Adam Gellerâ€™s time at the Teach For America training institute and publicly launched July 23, 2006. The concept stemmed from the idea that if Geller had the inclination to blog about his experience, it was likely that others did, too. It was Geller's belief that the collective voice of a community could resonate louder than blogging alone, however there was no existing site or mechanism for this to happen. Sometime in between lesson planning and copy-room runs, the site was born. In 2008, Teach For America began publicly recognizing Teach For Us as a source of finding out â€œwhat itâ€™s truly like to be a Teach For America corps memberâ€ by placing a link on its [The corps experience](http://teachforamerica.org/corps/index.htm) page. In September 2009, [Scholastic](http://www2.scholastic.com/browse/article.jsp?id=3752562) named TeachFor.Us "Best news from the trenches" on its list of the Top 20 Teacher Blogs. Teach For Us is generously hosted by [ibiblio](http://ibiblio.org).

Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Violence Policy Center (VPC) is a national tax-exempt organization that works to stop gun death and injury through research, education, advocacy, and collaboration. It informs the public about the impact of gun violence on their daily lives; exposes the profit-driven marketing and lobbying activities of the firearms industry and gun lobby; offers technical expertise to policymakers, organizations, and advocates on the federal, state, and local levels; and advocates for policies to reduce firearms violence. The organization publishes original studies on gun violence in the United States, with a focus on the firearms industry, gun violence data, the causes of gun violence, and public health approaches to reducing firearm death and injury. It informs the public of its research through targeted campaigns involving news media outreach, social media, and public events. The VPC partners with a diverse range of organizations working on gun violence prevention and related issues, and works with national, state, and local advocacy organizations representing affected constituencies such as women, children, minorities, consumers, and public health practitioners, with the aim of keeping the neighborhoods, homes, schools, and workplaces safe from gun violence. The Violence Policy Center was founded in 1988 by Josh Sugarmann and is based in Washington, District of Columbia.

Description: Running an organization can be challenging. RTA Group can give you the financial and accounting advice and support you need to succeed.
Full Description: RTA Group is an outsourced CFO and Accounting Services firm with corporate headquarters just outside Sacramento, California and serves the entirety of the United States. As former seasoned executives, we now help companies maximize their resources and take advantage of financial opportunities so that they can become – and remain – strong competitors in today’s highly charged business environment. Understanding that each of our clients has unique needs and expectations, we offer a highly customized approach to achieving financial efficiency, cash flow, strategic growth, and long-term stability. Our Outsourced Accounting Mission Transforming the way people view value related to outsourced accounting and finance. How are we different? Real Time Data Our services provide our clients with real time data so that they can make information-based decisions in real time.  We provide you with reporting packages and key performance indicators (KPI’s) that can help you make decisions that truly drive your business forward. Results Based Pricing This approach is no different than buying a nice dinner at your favorite restaurant.  When you order your meal, you know what you’re getting and how much it will cost before you make the purchase.  Could you imagine going to your favorite restaurant and paying for dinner based on how long it took them to prepare and serve your meal?  A traditional accounting firm does just that.  They prepare a bill based on how long it takes the accountant to perform the task.  We don’t think this is fair to you.  Hourly billing does not promote an emphasis on customer service or an incentive to complete jobs timely. Monthly Fees You pay a monthly fee only for the services you want and need. The fee does not change based on the number of phone calls or conversations that you have with our Staff. Technology to Add Value So many CPA firms are stuck in the past, utilizing outdated technology and services that provide very little value to their clients. They focus primarily on historical financial statements and tax returns.  At RTA Group, we utilize the latest technology to ensure that we are providing our clients with value.  Imagine if you knew how your performance stacked up against your competitors and others in your industry.  RTA Group can show you. Not a local company?  That’s ok, our firm was built to operate virtually and currently services clients throughout the United States.  The technology that we use, and our effective communication methods allow us to provide you valuable services as if we were right next door. Our Advantage … Your Success! We’ve spent our entire careers transforming finance and accounting functions into a competitive advantage. Our team has practical hands on experience at all levels across many different organizations and industries just like yours. We’ve been where you are, so we know the information you need and how to get it. When our clients come to us they are hungry for the real time data and cost savings that an efficient finance & accounting department can provide, and we provide just that. We’re ready to do the same for you!

Description: Comprehensive Psychiatric Associates, LLC was established to provide accessibility to quality mental health services for the Northland area.
Full Description: Comprehensive Psychiatric Associates, LLC was established to provide accessibility to quality mental health services for the Northland area. CPA was established in May 1998 in an effort to provide accessibility to quality mental health services for the Northland area. Since 1998, CPA has grown to include several Psychiatrists, Nurse Practitioners and therapists.  CPA's clientele encompasses patients from Western Kansas through Eastern Missouri. CPA offers routine outpatient psychiatric evaluation and treatment, individual and family therapy as well as support groups. CPA's providers are all Board Certified/Eligible and Residency/Fellowship trained. CPA's expertise is broad and includes treatment from pediatric age to the mature adult population.  CPA has worked hard to forge relationships with most commercial insurance plans and they are paneled with a majority of the insurance carriers here in the greater Kansas City metropolitan area.  All providers at CPA credential individually with each insurance plan, so while one or more of their providers might be paneled with a particular plan it does not necessarily indicate that every provider is a network provider with each plan. If you want to maximize the network benefits through your insurance plan you will need to call your carrier prior to scheduling an appointment with any CPA provider, to ensure that particular provider is indeed networked with your insurance plan. Ultimately it is the primary responsibility of the patient to verify network status.

Description: CartiONE is the first cartilage repair technology that uses patient’s own chondrocytes to generate hyaline cartilage in one surgery.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: CartiONE is the first cartilage repair technology that uses patient’s own chondrocytes to generate hyaline cartilage in one surgery. Cartilage Repair Systems (CRS) is a newly established Joint Preservation company developing and commercialising technologies in the fields of Orthopaedic Sports Medicine.   In March 2017, CRS acquired CellCoTec B.V in the Netherlands. Its core technology is CartiONE, a ONE hour service that provides surgeons with the patient’s own (autologous) freshly isolated chondrocytes and bone marrow cells for use in ONE surgical procedure. This cell service can be used with all other commercially available chondral / osteo-chondral membranes or scaffolds. Cartione is available in both the USA and the EU.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Information Technology, Science and Engineering, Sports
